<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<document>
    <title>Introduction to XML</title>
    <section>
        <title>What is XML?</title>
        <paragraph>XML (eXtensible Markup Language) is a markup language that defines a set of rules for encoding documents in a format that is both human-readable and machine-readable.</paragraph>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Key Features of XML</title>
        <list>
            <item>Self-descriptive structure</item>
            <item>Platform-independent</item>
            <item>Supports hierarchical data representation</item>
            <item>Extensible and customizable</item>
        </list>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Common Uses of XML</title>
        <list>
            <item>Data storage and transport</item>
            <item>Configuration files</item>
            <item>Web services (e.g., SOAP)</item>
            <item>Document formatting (e.g., XHTML)</item>
        </list>
    </section>
</document>